

>> Dockerize application â†’ build image
>> Push image to registry (Docker Hub/ECR/GCR)
>> Deploy container using Kubernetes (manifest or Helm)


****After creating Dockerfile, build the image
    $ docker build -t my-node-app:1.0 .

****Run locally to test 
    $ docker run -p 3000:3000 my-node-app:1.0

****Tag and Push to repo
    $ docker tag my-node-app:1.0 <username>/my-node-app:1.0
    $ docker push <username>/my-node-app:1.0
  If using ECR, login before pushing.
    $ aws ecr get-login-password | docker login


**** Manage deployments using kubernetes with deployment/service.yaml

    $ kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml
    $ kubectl apply -f service.yaml






